Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring a medium #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @bell pepper{1} lengthwise; remove stem and seeds. Thinly slice @chives{1/4%ounce}. Tear @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into bite-size pieces.

Rub each bell pepper half with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on a #baking sheet{}, cut sides down.

Roast on top rack until softened and lightly charred, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Remove from oven and let cool slightly. Transfer to a #cutting board{}, then thinly slice.

Heat broiler to high.

== Panko Topping ==

While bell pepper roasts, place @butter{1%tablespoon} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until just melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and season with salt.

> Use 2 tablespoons butter for 4 servings instead of 1.

== Pasta ==

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Drain and set aside.

== Shrimp ==

While pasta cooks, rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water and pat dry with paper towels. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large, preferably #ovenproof pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add shrimp and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until opaque and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Sauce ==

While pasta cooks, heat a large, preferably ovenproof pan over medium-high heat. Add @marinara cup{14%ounce}, 1/2 cup water, half the chives, a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}, and a big pinch of salt; stir to combine. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} until melted and combined. Season with salt and pepper.

> Use pan used for shrimp here.

== Assemble and Broil ==

Stir sliced bell pepper and drained cavatappi into pan with sauce. If sauce seems too thick, add a splash of water. Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with mozzarella and panko.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture now to a baking dish.

Broil on top rack until cheese melts and panko is golden brown, ~{2-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Sprinkle with remaining chives and more chili flakes if desired. Divide between plates and serve.

> Stir shrimp into pan with bell pepper and cavatappi.